dialogue.speech: maze

name: gnomes
friendlyGreeting: Good tidings, good trades, good tales, to you good day.
neutralGreeting: Long shadows cross our path today. Mind where your steps fall, travelers.
friendlyFarewell: Go well, friends of Aenen... may luck skip ahead of you.

dialogue.speech: Aenen stands strong and stubborn. The Maze will not conquer us.
A deal? Perhaps. We'll hear you out...
The road forgets no footsteps.
Trade winds blow through Ichiba, aye.
They call it a realm of honor. We call it a realm that forgets its own shadows.
He speaks of honor as if it were a cloak he never removes.
Where he walks, trouble walks two steps behind.
Anger is a small cloak, but you wear it bravely.
Ask them for honesty and they’ll steal the question right back.
He of many words and even more wares.
Subtlety is a language they never learned.
Gnomes of Aenen walk sideways through the world. Straight paths are for taller folk.
Mind where your steps fall, travelers.
Every corner whispers a different secret… most of them half-true.
Some fear her, some flatter her.
Even the shadows owe him favors.

They speak of honor, yes... just before they pounce. Hypocrisy makes a fine mane.
If war comes, it will be because the lions wanted applause for starting it.
Pickett counts everything: coin, favors, enemies...
If you seek purpose, look under whatever stones you dare to lift.
Half of what he sells is junk, the other half trouble.
Rumours flutter like moths. Catch one and another slips past.
Even the walls in his tavern have opinions.
No need for thanks.
Ask again tomorrow; I might be someone different by then.

name: leonals
friendlyGreeting: Blessings upon thee; thy presence is ever a welcome sight.
neutralGreeting: Move aside, stranger, lest thou hinder the Lady's own work.
friendlyFarewell: Go in the Lady's grace, friends, and return when thou hast need.
neutralFarewell: Go thy way, and may no folly follow thee.

dialogue.speech: Aenen is a den of gnomish intrigue, ever scheming, ever pressing us toward the brink of war, reckless of the consequences of their actions.
Speak thy needs plainly, and we shall see what may be bartered in honor.
Go thy way, and may no folly follow thee.
Their dealings are ever shrouded in petty scheming.

Much endureth by our shield-arm and our great fortress. 
But for our watch upon the crater's edge, this domain would have long since been swallowed whole.
Let none here forget whose vigilance holdeth the darkness at bay.
Steadfast in duty and unwavering in The Lady's light.
A villain unworthy of mercy.
Mind thy tongue, wretch, lest honour compel me to silence it.
There is no honour amongst thieves.
He is no threat, merely an irritation.
Trust them not overmuch; their loyalty shifteth with the scent of meat.

Beware their false courtesy, traveler.
Aenen's schemes have near drawn steel more times than I can count.
Blessings upon thee.
A strange crossroads, indeed, where virtue must stand guard at every hour.
A perilous sorceress, weaving powers best left untouched.
A villain unworthy of mercy.
She who tempereth justice with mercy guideth every true heart.
Leonals stand where others falter; our honor is our armor, our duty our guide.
Avarice cloudeth his judgment.
There are always shadows to be driven back in the Lady's name.
A gnoll trader of dubious repute.
Tensions rise between the realms, and many fear steel shall speak ere long.
We lodge there when duty requireth; his hospitality is humble but sound.
Thy courtesy is welcome.
We are knights of Danaos, sworn to the White Lady and unbending in our charge.

name: chamber of commerce
friendlyGreeting: Heard good things about you. Keep that up and we'll get along fine.
neutralGreeting: Slow it down, outsider. We keep order here, for everyone.
friendlyFarewell: See you around. Holler if you need backup.
neutralFarewell: We're done here. Stay out of trouble.

dialogue.speech: Not now. I'm on the clock.
We're done here. Stay out of trouble.
The Chamber runs this city. Make sure you remember it.
Talks too much about virtue for my taste.
Emmons? Yeah, there's coin on his head. Report any information to HQ.
Say that again and you'll be spitting teeth on the cobbles.
Guild scum slip through cracks, but we close those cracks fast.
If you want exotic junk, he’s your gnome.
We keep them in line easy enough. They yap and posture, then bolt when steel comes out.
Half of them are harmless, the other half are dangerous...
We keep the peace here, remember that.
Everything you see here exists because the Chamber keeps the wheels turning.
Not Chamber business, so not my problem.
Wouldn't mind the bounty myself, but he's a slippery bastard.
Good intentions don’t keep streets safe for trade. We do.
He runs the Chamber, which means he runs this city.
We're guards, not recruiters. Try the notice boards if you want busywork.
If you’re buying from Red Ear, check the goods twice.
They say the Guild’s planning something big. Not my problem unless it hits the streets.
A steady fellow, that one.
Just doing my job.
Pay my wage for the week and maybe I’ll share my life story.

name: gnolls
friendlyGreeting: Heh, I smell you from far. Is good smell today.
neutralGreeting: You no enemy... maybe. We watch you close.
friendlyFarewell: Go safe, friend-pack. We howl for your return.

dialogue.speech: Show what you bring, then we see who smiles.
Strangers go now.
Commerce-people think they own everything.
Hrrf. Too proud.
We hear he got price on head. Big price.
Hrrf. Maybe you want fight… or you just stupid.
Cowards who fear real hunt.
Try sell us shiny junk. We laugh, he leave quick.

We Gnolls strong-pack. Hunt hard, fight hard, live wild.
Gnolls no bow to city laws. Jungle give law, we follow.
Too many toys, not enough claws.
We watch you close.
Guards stare like we already bite someone.

What about her?
She a great sorceress. You be scared.
Just big sneak with fancy name.
They step in our jungle, they get lost fast.
City boss-man count coins all day.
Jungle always got things need killing. If you tough enough.
He got good nose for deals.
Hrrf. Jungle whisper plenty. You go listen.
Inn-man always listening.
Thanks mean nothing in jungle.
Gnolls born in jungle, gnolls die in jungle.

name: goblins
friendlyGreeting: No blades for these in the alleys, lads.
neutralGreeting: Fog and shadows to you, stranger. Stay tidy in the lanes.
friendlyFarewell: Catch you in the lanes later. Drinks if we both survive.
neutralFarewell: Off you trot, and mind the eyes in the brickwork.

dialogue.speech: Coin’s coin, culley. Let’s see what shines for what jangles.
Off you trot now.
Commerce boys don’t step in our alleys. Too slippery for their boots.
He’s honest… too honest. Makes my teeth itch just lookin' at him.
The Hand runs the quiet jobs… the kind you don’t brag about unless you like shallow graves.
Big words from someone so easy to cut.
If you gotta ask, you ain't deep in the lanes yet.
That shiny little diplomat's got more silver in his tongue than in his purse.
They’re loud, they’re dumb, and they bite.
I don’t mind 'em. Easy to lift from, hard to catch.
Fog and shadows to you.
You want honest work? Wrong city. You want opportunity? Welcome.
Wizards with bad attitudes make lousy neighbors.
Streets listen when he whispers.
Leonals? Pah. Big furry paladins with sticks shoved so far up they walk like statues.
Got ledgers where his heart should be.
Work’s always lurkin'. Depends how dirty you’re willin' to get your boots.
Sells good junk and bad junk... sometimes in the same sack.
Heard whispers of a fat purse wanderin' the market… and a blade followin' it.
Runs a clean taproom... too clean, if you ask me.
Yeah yeah. We're square.
Just another lane-rat tryin' to stay one step ahead of sharper blades.
